charges.charge_description: On or about June 17, 2015, in the Western District of Missouri, the defendant, KENNETH J. DILLON, a/k/a Kenneth J. Steinman, having been convicted of a crime punishable by imprisonment for a term exceeding one year, did knowingly possess, in and affecting interstate commerce, ammunition, to wit:   eight (8) live rounds of Federal Premium Ammunition brand, .40 caliber ammunition, contrary to the provisions of Title 18, United States Code, Sections 922(g)(1) and 924(a)(2).
